InformedConsent:
Welcome to Our Study!    

This consent form asks you to take part in a research study. The study is being conducted by Felipe De Brigard, PhD., associate professor at the Department of Philosophy, the Center for Cognitive Neuroscience, and the Duke Institute for Brain Sciences.

 

Purpose: This research study seeks to help us understand the ways in which memory and imagination interact.

 

What you will be asked to do: This research study consists of one session. You will be asked to read a passage and then to answer some questions about it. The total time for participating in this research study is expected to take between 15 and 30 minutes. At the end of the study, you will be paid $4.50. Participation in this study is voluntary, and you can stop at any time without penalty, but you will only be compensated for your time if you get to the end of each session and submit your HIT. To withdraw from the study, click on the “Return HIT” button, or close your browser window.

 

How your confidentiality will be maintained: If you choose to participate, your name will not be linked to your responses at any time, and there is no link between this consent form and your responses. However, we will collect your Amazon Mechanical Turk worker identification number for payment purposes and record keeping. All data will be securely saved at all times. All data we keep will be de-identified, indefinitely.

 

Benefits and Risks: This research will not benefit you personally. The researcher will be happy to discuss the details of the study with you in detail at its completion.  We know of no risks to you for participating in this study.  

 

If you have any questions about this research, please ask the experimenter who set up this “HIT”.  You may also contact the IMC Lab at imagination-study@duke.edu if you have any questions. For questions about your rights in this study, contact the Duke IRB at campusirb@duke.edu

 

Clicking Accept: By clicking on the “I consent” button, you indicate that you are 18 years of age or older, that you voluntarily agree to participate in this study and that you understand the information in this consent form. You have not waived any legal rights you otherwise would have as a participant in a research study.
